         <abstract>
            <p>We give a heuristic argument, supported by numerical evidence, which suggests that the maximum, taken over the reduced residue classes modulo $k$, of the least prime in the class, is usually about $\phi(k) \log k \log \phi(k)$, where $\phi$ is Euler's phi-function.</p>
